comments: Durant's (BKN) foot makes incidental contact with the ball.
Brunson (DAL) legally contests Irving's (BKN) jump shot attempt.

Griffin (BKN) reaches in and marginal contact occurs to Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) front prior to the release of his dribble.
Irving (BKN) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) is not established outside of the RA when contact occurs during Irving's (BKN) driving shot attempt.
Durant (BKN) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Powell (DAL) makes contact with Irving's (BKN) arm during his driving shot attempt.

Harris (BKN) commits a take foul on Hardaway Jr. (DAL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contests Irving's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) naturally loses possession of the ball.

Replay review of the foul called on Brunson (DAL) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was incorrectly deemed unsuccessful and the call should have been overturned. The call was upheld because of contact made by Brunson to Green?s (BKN) wrist/arm after first making contact with the ball. Given the additional contact, the play was deemed to have not met the standard for clear and conclusive evidence to overturn the call. However, upon further review, the initial ball contact was enough to dislodge and affect Green?s shot attempt and the subsequent contact should have been deemed incidental to a legal basketball movement.
Irving (BKN) commits a take foul on Hardaway Jr. (DAL).
